Subject: I&C STARTUP ENGINEER


> I&C STARTUP ENGINEER
>
> ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS: Under the direction of Start-up Supervisor, is
> responsible for the implementation of the Start-up I/C test program. This
> includes reviewing plant engineering documents and P&ID's, performing
> calibration and troubleshooting of the I/C equipment, assigning work to
> O.E.C. Start-up I/C Technician and construction craftsmen in support of
> start-up testing activities. Works with equipment vendors and interfaces
> with NEPCO engineering and construction departments as required. Scopes
> project drawings for turnover packages.
>
>
> ESSENTIAL REQUIREMENTS: Operates from established and well-known
procedures
> under general directions. Job is not supervisory in nature. Receives
> minimum supervision. Decisions are made within policy constraints. Not
> accountable for budget preparation or compliance. No operating budget. New
> and varied work situations. Job involves a moderate degree of complexity.
> Contacts are normally made with others inside the Company. Contacts are
> usually immediate associates and own supervisor.
>
>
> PREFERRED SKILLS: Must be able to read electrical blueprints, I/C data
> sheets, logic drawings and utilize typical test equipment associated with
> this position. Good communication skills (oral and written) helpful.
> Education requirements include: A.A.S. or 4 year engineering degree or
> equivalent. 8 or more years experience in major power plant equipment and
> system installations. Knowledge of labor jurisdiction, construction
> techniques, tools and equipment, and protective tagging systems required.
> Working knowledge of a power plant and associated systems. Previous
> experience in checkout or design of Distributed Control Systems a must.
> Knowledge of power plant processes recommended.
>
>
> SPECIAL CHARACTERISTICS: The duties and responsibilities are generally
> performed in a plant or support services environment. The position
> generally involves occasional sitting; frequent standing, occasional
> walking; moderate to heavy lifting, and carrying; frequent kneeling,
> twisting and balancing; occasional climbing; and, frequent reaching,
> pushing/pulling, grasping and operation of heavy equipment and machinery.
> The environmental conditions generally include ambient inside temperature
> and lighting levels and hazardous conditions. The use of protective
> clothing and/or personal devices is generally required.
>
>
> CONTACT: HR@nepco.com
>
>
